  "text": "The HTTP filter chain extension mechanism in Envoy is defined across several C++ source files organized into key components:\n\n**Filter Factory Registry and Interfaces (envoy/http/ and envoy/server/):**\n- envoy/http/filter.h defines the core FilterChainFactoryCallbacks interface and filter status enums that control filter chain iteration\n- envoy/http/filter_factory.h defines FilterContext (configuration name and filter name), FilterFactoryCb (factory function type), FilterChainManager (sink for filter creation), and FilterChainFactory (creates filter chains for new streams)\n- envoy/server/filter_config.h defines NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory and UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory interfaces that factories must implement to be registered in the extension registry\n\n**Filter Chain Execution Engine (source/common/http/):**\n- source/common/http/filter_manager.h contains FilterManager which implements per-request filter chain execution, ActiveStreamFilterBase for tracking filter state, and FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl which implements the callbacks used to add filters to a chain\n- source/common/http/filter_manager.cc provides the implementation of filter chain iteration, status handling, and data flow through decoder/encoder filters\n- source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h provides FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories() which creates filter chains from factory configurations, and FilterChainHelper template for processing filter configurations\n- source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h/cc defines ConnectionManagerImpl which creates new streams and initiates filter chain creation\n- source/common/http/conn_manager_config.h provides configuration structures for the connection manager\n- source/common/http/dependency_manager.h/cc manages filter dependencies and validation\n\n**Dynamic Filter Configuration (source/common/filter/):**\n- source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h defines NamedHttpFilterFactoryCb (struct containing filter name and factory function), HttpDynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl for dynamic filter configuration discovery, and DynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl for runtime filter configuration updates\n- source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.cc implements dynamic filter configuration subscription and instantiation\n\n**HTTP Connection Manager Extension (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/):**\n- source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h/cc defines HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory which creates the HTTP connection manager network filter and initializes the filter chain factory using FilterChainHelper\n\n**Upstream Filter Chain (source/common/router/):**\n- source/common/router/router.h defines FilterConfig which implements Http::FilterChainFactory for upstream request filter chains, creating chains for requests sent to upstream clusters\n\nThe execution flow: When a new HTTP stream arrives, the connection manager calls FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain(), which invokes FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb() with FilterContext and FilterFactoryCb. The FilterManager's FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl receives these callbacks and adds filters via addStreamDecoderFilter/addStreamEncoderFilter/addStreamFilter. During stream processing, FilterManager executes the filter chain by iterating through filters, checking return status codes (Continue, StopIteration, etc.) to control iteration, and managing buffering and data flow. The FilterContext carries metadata about each filter (config_name, filter_name) through the chain."
}

